The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Valencia scores on debut
                                                   Valencia scores on debut
                      
	 Berlin: Ecuadorian winger Antonio Valencia scored on his Manchester United debut in a 2-1 win over Boca Juniors on Wednesday.         
	The friendly is part of a four-team tournament in Munich that also includes Bayern Munich and AC Milan. United play Bayern on Thursday after the Germans defeated AC Milan 4-1.               
	 Munich: Bayern Munich said they have finalised a severance agreement with Juergen Klinsmann on Thursday, three months after the coach was dismissed.               
	 Madrid: Barcelona midfielder Aleksandr Hleb has agreed a one-year loan move to former club VfB Stuttgart, the clubs said on Thursday. Hleb had originally been included in the Zlatan Ibrahimovic- Samuel Eto swap deal but said he preferred a return to the Bundesliga and his old club Stuttgart.               
	 London: Arsenal midfielder Tomas Rosicky has picked up a minor injury problem since making his comeback earlier this month after nearly 18 months out.               
	 Bucharest: Romanian prosecutors have charged the owner of CFR Cluj football club with blackmail and supporting a criminal group.               
	 Birmingham: The Indian hockey team began their tour of Europe on a losing note, suffering a 1-3 defeat against England in the rain-soaked opening encounter of the three-match Test series here.         
	Ben Hawes (first minute), Barry Middleton (18th) and Richard Smith (68th) scored for the hosts, while Dhananjay Mahadik (eighth) was on target for India.               
	 New Delhi: The top seed pair of Rupesh Kumar and Sanave Thomas in mens doubles and Aparna Balan and Shruti Kurian in womens doubles, made the semis of the New Zealand Open Grand Prix badminton tournament in Auckland Thursday. Anand Pawar bowed out in the mens singles quarter finals.               
	 New Delhi: National record holder discus thrower Seema Antil qualified for next months Berlin World Athletics Championships after she crossed the B qualifying standard by winning gold in the Loughborough European Permit Meet at Leicestershire.               
	 New Delhi: Over 235 players from 14 countries, including India, will be vying for honours in six age groups at the ONGC Asian Youth Chess Championship to be held here from August 2 to 9.           AGENCIES                                                                                                                   
